---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Top 10 Banished Leader Powers Ranked - Halo Wars 2";
const description = "A subjective ranking of the top 10 active Banished leader powers in Halo Wars 2. From Grunt Dome to Cataclysm, discover which powers dominate the battlefield.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 1, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-01";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="BtfL8SOQ5Nw"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    This is a subjective ranking of the top 10 <strong>active</strong> leader powers for The Banished in Halo Wars 2. No passive abilities like Combat Repair - only powers you can drop on the battlefield.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">#10: Grunt Dome (Yap Yap)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Grunt Dome is an excellent defensive tool that protects your units AND your allies' units:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Works great for canceling out beams (especially Level 1 beams)</li>
    <li>Defends against turret fire, siege, and other attacks</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Fully upgraded (Level 3)</strong>: Get two Grunt Domes</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scarab Combo</strong>: Drop first dome, wait for depletion, drop second, then use Scarab's Y ability for effectively three shields</li>
    <li>Lets Scarab last incredibly long under fire</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#9: Methane Party (Yap Yap)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Similar to Forge's Scatter Bomb, Methane Party offers versatile utility:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Impacts both buildings and units</li>
    <li>Applies debuff to enemies</li>
    <li>Buffs Yap Yap's Grunt units</li>
    <li>Effective on buildings AND units (unlike some powers that favor one)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#8: Decimus Hero Drop</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The 11 o'clock ability for Decimus brings a powerful hero unit to the battlefield:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hero unit is great overall</li>
    <li>Y ability with beams is incredible - like a mini-Eradication</li>
    <li>Works excellently on maps like Sentry for turtling</li>
    <li>Great against bundled units</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#7: Atriox's Bulwark / Shipmaster's Extraction (Tie)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Both powers offer invulnerability protection in different ways:</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Bulwark (Atriox)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Great for baiting and canceling enemy leader powers</li>
    <li>Short invincibility window</li>
    <li>Cancel Mac Blasts, Beams, and other quick powers</li>
    <li>Protects bases from Vulture Mega-Barrage</li>
    <li>Forces opponent to wait for cooldowns after you negate their attacks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Extraction (Shipmaster)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Works defensively or offensively</li>
    <li>Can heal your base</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#6: Hunter's Brand (Colony)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Hunter's Brand is a devastating ability when used correctly:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Deletes armies when fully upgraded</li>
    <li>Works best on units, not buildings</li>
    <li>Excellent against infantry and vehicles</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Bug Warning</strong>: If dropped too close to Fog of War and your last unit dies, it cancels and counts as used (wastes resources AND cooldown)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#5: Eradication (Atriox)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">One of the most spectacular powers in the game:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Spectacular to watch destroy units and buildings</li>
    <li>Slow-building power with beams converging to big implosion</li>
    <li>Works great on both units and buildings</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combo</strong>: Pair with Voridus's Maelstrom - opponent's army gets annihilated regardless of what they do</li>
    <li>No real complaints with this power</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#4: Lich Vanguard (Pavium)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Often called "the Flying Scarab," Lich Vanguard is an incredibly versatile power:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Beam sounds and looks very similar to Scarab's main cannon</li>
    <li>Flies around continuously attacking and destroying</li>
    <li>Works great on buildings too</li>
    <li>Creates a unit bubble on the battlefield where you can train units</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Underrated Feature</strong>: Train Hunters, Reavers, and other units directly on the field</li>
    <li>One of the longest-lasting leader powers in the game</li>
    <li>If opponent ignores it, it annihilates everything in its path</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#3: Devastating Host (Colony)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The <strong>best unit drop in the game</strong>:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Drops tons of veteran units with vehicle symbiotes</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Bonus</strong>: Can activate symbiotes on existing units you drop it on top of (e.g., your Wraiths get symbiotes too)</li>
    <li>Symbiotes overall are underrated for buffing Colony's vehicles</li>
    <li>Veteran units from this drop are exceptional</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#2: Glassing Beam</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">An iconic and devastating power that strikes fear into opponents:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Incredible in Halo Wars 2</li>
    <li>Campaign gives you nightmares of beams</li>
    <li>Menace on the battlefield in multiplayer</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Sweet Spot</strong>: Beam Level 2 (Beam 3 takes too long to wind up)</li>
    <li>Too many players don't split units when getting beamed - lose entire armies</li>
    <li>Works best on units (okay on buildings)</li>
    <li>Has gotten buffed over time rather than nerfed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#1: Cataclysm (Voridus)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The most powerful Banished leader power, Cataclysm is absolutely devastating:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Activates all infusion on the battlefield causing it to rupture/explode</li>
    <li>Similar to Kinsano's Inferno but deals much more damage</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combos with infusion-spreading units</strong>: Wraith (with infusion tech), Infused Engineers, Volatile Scarab, infusion leader power</li>
    <li>Stack with Invigorating Frenzy for infusion healing</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Can destroy entire bases</strong></li>
    <li>Works on units too - nothing really stands a chance</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ultimate Combo</strong>: Maelstrom + Cataclysm = absolute devastation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Here's the complete ranking of the top 10 Banished leader powers:</p>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Cataclysm (Voridus)</strong> - Infusion explosion devastation</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Glassing Beam</strong> - Iconic and terrifying</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Devastating Host (Colony)</strong> - Best unit drop in the game</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lich Vanguard (Pavium)</strong> - The Flying Scarab</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Eradication (Atriox)</strong> - Spectacular destruction</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hunter's Brand (Colony)</strong> - Army deleter</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Bulwark/Extraction (Atriox/Shipmaster)</strong> - Invulnerability protection</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Decimus Hero Drop</strong> - Mini-Eradication hero</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Methane Party (Yap Yap)</strong> - Versatile debuff/buff</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grunt Dome (Yap Yap)</strong> - Shield protection</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4 mt-6">
    Each of these powers can turn the tide of battle when used effectively. Master their timing and combos to dominate your opponents on the battlefield!
  </p>

</BlogPostLayout>
